  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-01 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment: all factors assessed, credibility scores reviewed by the assessment team. Decision: Accepted. This package is a synthetic adversarial sample targeting W-AR-01: one credibility factor (Model form) carries a requiredLevel without a corresponding structured acceptanceCriteria field, relying instead on an extensive narrative rationale that may give reviewers false confidence that acceptance criteria are formally documented.",
